item.description:
This memo explains the required steps to write you own shellcode. From C code (or assembly directly) to the shellcode's string. At the bottom of this page a code is present to test your shellcode.
x86_64 Shellcode In this memo, the shellcode will launch /bin/sh. Let's take the following C code :
#include  int main(void){ execve("/bin/sh", NULL, NULL); } NULL parameters stands for args and environment, we don't need them for now.
